-- Zain of Kuwait Is in Talks With Etisalat to Sell Stake, Seyassah Reports
-- Fiona MacDonald
-- 2010-06-27T05:10:39Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-27/zain-of-kuwait-is-in-talks-with-etisalat-to-sell-stake-seyassah-reports.html

          
          
             Mobile Telecommunications Co., the
Kuwaiti phone company known as Zain, is in talks with Emirates
Telecommunications Corp. to sell a majority stake in Zain Group,
 Al-Seyassah  reported, without saying where it got the
information.  
 A Zain delegation met last week with officials at the
United Arab Emirates phone company, according to the newspaper.  
 Zain Chief Executive Officer Nabil bin Salama said June 8
the company completed a $9 billion sale of most of its African
operations to Bharti Airtel Ltd. Zain is not in talks to sell a
stake, bin Salama told a news conference at the time.  
